Nov 10 2004	I don't think I would stay there again	My husband and me just came back from our little London vacation. We spent 5 nights at the “Blades Hotel” (near the Victoria station). I would like to share few comments with the others, because for us it was an unpleasant surprise.1.When we arrived we discovered that there are no phones in the rooms. We were irritated because by paying $136 per night (may be not horribly expansive, but still not very cheap) we did not expect that have a phone in the room should be a problem.2.We have stayed in a number of European’s hotels, but I have never seen such a tiny bathroom. In order to pull up your pants or if you need to dry yourself up with a towel after the shower, you have to open the door into the room, because it’s not possible otherwise.3.We stayed there for 5 nights and our bed sheets were not changed even ones (!!!)The towels were changed on the 4th day of our stay (!!!). Of course there are some good things to say: location is perfect, breakfast is good, staff is friendly and helpful.	
